---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const post = {
  title: 'TOPCon vs Mono PERC vs HJT vs Polycrystalline: Which Solar Panel is Right for India in 2025?',
  excerpt: 'A data-driven comparison of the four major solar cell technologies — efficiency, temperature performance, 25-year yield, degradation, and price — with India-specific analysis.',
  category: 'Technical Deep-Dive',
  date: '2025-05-30',
  readTime: '14 min read',
  author: {
    name: 'Mr. Ramanadane C',
    role: 'Director, Ermis Consultants & Traders Pvt Ltd',
    bio: 'An experienced professional with extensive expertise in the textile value chain and international trade, Mr. Ramanadane C brings a global perspective to renewable energy procurement and project strategy.',
  },
};
---

<PageLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Ermis Global Blog`}
  description={post.excerpt}
>

  <!-- Article header -->
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">

    <!-- Breadcrumb -->
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-xs text-neutral-muted mb-8">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-red transition-colors">Home</a>
      <span>›</span>
      <a href="/blog" class="hover:text-brand-red transition-colors">Blog</a>
      <span>›</span>
      <span class="text-neutral-ink">TOPCon vs PERC vs HJT</span>
    </nav>

    <!-- Category + meta -->
    <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 mb-5">
      <span class="text-xs font-semibold px-3 py-1 rounded-full bg-brand-pale text-brand-red border border-brand-red/20">
        {post.category}
      </span>
      <span class="text-xs text-neutral-muted">{new Date(post.date).toLocaleDateString('en-IN', { day:'numeric', month:'long', year:'numeric' })}</span>
      <span class="text-xs text-neutral-muted">·</span>
      <span class="text-xs text-neutral-muted">{post.readTime}</span>
    </div>

    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-extrabold text-neutral-ink leading-tight mb-6">
      TOPCon vs Mono PERC vs HJT vs Polycrystalline:<br class="hidden md:block"/>
      <span class="text-brand-red">Which Solar Panel is Right for India in 2025?</span>
    </h1>

    <p class="text-lg text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed mb-8">
      India's rooftops bake at 65–80 °C in summer. The solar panel technology you choose
      determines not just how much power you generate on day one — but how much you'll generate
      in year 15 and year 25, when the real ROI is won or lost. This guide compares all four
      technologies with hard data, India-specific analysis, and a clear verdict for every use case.
    </p>

    <!-- Author -->
    <div class="flex items-start gap-4 p-5 bg-neutral-snow rounded-xl border border-neutral-rule mb-12">
      <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-brand-red flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-lg flex-shrink-0">
        R
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-ink text-sm">{post.author.name}</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-brand-red mb-1">{post.author.role}</p>
        <p class="text-xs text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed">{post.author.bio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- TL;DR box -->
    <div class="bg-neutral-ink rounded-2xl p-6 mb-12">
      <p class="text-brand-light text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">TL;DR — Key Takeaways</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-white/80">
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-brand-light flex-shrink-0">→</span> <span><strong class="text-white">Polycrystalline is effectively dead</strong> — 0% global market share in 2024. Not available from tier-1 manufacturers.</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-brand-light flex-shrink-0">→</span> <span><strong class="text-white">TOPCon dominates 2025</strong> with 60–75% global market share and the best cost-to-performance ratio.</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-brand-light flex-shrink-0">→</span> <span><strong class="text-white">HJT wins in heat</strong> — its -0.24%/°C temperature coefficient outperforms PERC by 31% in India's 65 °C module temperatures.</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-brand-light flex-shrink-0">→</span> <span><strong class="text-white">Mono PERC is being phased out</strong> — declining from 63% share (2023) to 43% (2024). Avoid for new installs where 25-year support matters.</span></li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-brand-light flex-shrink-0">→</span> <span><strong class="text-white">For most Indian projects, specify TOPCon</strong>. For Rajasthan, Gujarat, or roof-constrained premium installs, HJT's premium is justified.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- SECTION 1: Technology Overview -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-ink mb-4 mt-12">1. What Are These Technologies?</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
      All four technologies convert sunlight into electricity using silicon wafers, but the way each
      cell is designed to capture and retain electrons differs significantly — and those differences
      compound dramatically over 25 years in India's climate.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-5 mb-10">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-rule p-5">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-neutral-200 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold text-neutral-muted">Poly</div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-ink">Polycrystalline (Multi-Si)</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed">Made from multiple silicon crystals melted together. The crystal boundaries act as recombination sites, limiting efficiency. Lower manufacturing cost, but higher heat sensitivity and faster degradation. <strong class="text-neutral-ink">Discontinued by all tier-1 manufacturers as of 2023.</strong></p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-brand-red/30 bg-brand-pale p-5">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-brand-red/20 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold text-brand-red">PERC</div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-ink">Mono PERC (P-type)</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed">Mono-crystalline silicon with a <em>Passivated Emitter and Rear Cell</em> layer that reflects unabsorbed light back through the cell. P-type doping causes Light-Induced Degradation (LID) in year 1. The industry workhorse from 2018–2023, now rapidly losing ground.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-brand-red/30 bg-brand-pale p-5">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-brand-red/20 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold text-brand-red">TOP</div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-ink">TOPCon (N-type)</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed">N-type mono-silicon with a ultra-thin <em>Tunnel Oxide Passivated Contact</em> layer on the rear. Eliminates LID entirely. Manufactureable on existing PERC lines with ~15% capex upgrade — which is why adoption exploded. Now accounts for 60–75% of global production in 2024.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-ink/20 bg-neutral-snow p-5">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-lg bg-neutral-ink/10 flex items-center justify-center text-xs font-bold text-neutral-ink">HJT</div>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-neutral-ink">HJT / SHJ (N-type)</h3>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sm text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed"><em>Heterojunction Technology</em> sandwiches thin amorphous silicon layers around an N-type mono-crystalline core. Achieves the lowest temperature coefficient of any commercial silicon technology (-0.24%/°C), outstanding bifaciality (92–95%), and minimal degradation. Premium price, premium performance — especially in hot climates.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- SECTION 2: Efficiency -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-ink mb-2 mt-12">2. Module Efficiency: Commercial vs Lab Records</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-muted mb-6">Commercial module efficiencies (STC, 25°C) — what you actually buy today. Source: NREL, manufacturer datasheets 2024–25.</p>

    <!-- Efficiency bar chart SVG -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl bg-neutral-snow border border-neutral-rule p-6 mb-4">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-neutral-muted mb-5">Module Efficiency Range — Commercial Modules (2025)</p>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 680 280" class="w-full" role="img" aria-label="Bar chart comparing commercial module efficiency of four solar cell technologies">
        <!-- Grid lines -->
        <line x1="120" y1="20" x2="640" y2="20" stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1"/>
        <line x1="120" y1="70" x2="640" y2="70" stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1"/>
        <line x1="120" y1="120" x2="640" y2="120" stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1"/>
        <line x1="120" y1="170" x2="640" y2="170" stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1"/>
        <line x1="120" y1="220" x2="640" y2="220" stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1"/>

        <!-- Y-axis labels -->
        <text x="110" y="24" text-anchor="end" font-size="11" fill="#6B7280">28%</text>
        <text x="110" y="74" text-anchor="end" font-size="11" fill="#6B7280">24%</text>
        <text x="110" y="124" text-anchor="end" font-size="11" fill="#6B7280">20%</text>
        <text x="110" y="174" text-anchor="end" font-size="11" fill="#6B7280">16%</text>
        <text x="110" y="224" text-anchor="end" font-size="11" fill="#6B7280">12%</text>

        <!-- Bar: Poly (14-17%, avg 15.5%) — scale: 28% = 200px, so 1% = 7.14px -->
        <!-- 14% = 200 - (14-12)/16 * 200 = ... let me use: bottom=220, 0%=220, 28%=20, so 1%=7.14px. y = 220 - (val-12)*7.14, but start from 12% -->
        <!-- Actually simpler: chart from 12% to 28% = 16% range = 200px height. 1% = 12.5px -->
        <!-- y_bottom = 220. val% -> y = 220 - (val - 12) * 12.5 -->
        <!-- Poly range: 14-17%: bottom y = 220-(14-12)*12.5=195, top y=220-(17-12)*12.5=157.5, height=37.5 -->

        <!-- Poly bar -->
        <rect x="145" y="157" width="80" height="63" rx="4" fill="#D1D5DB"/>
        <text x="185" y="152" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="600" fill="#6B7280">14–17%</text>
        <text x="185" y="243" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#6B7280">Polycrystalline</text>
        <text x="185" y="257" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#9CA3AF">Discontinued</text>

        <!-- PERC range: 20-22.5%: y_bottom=220-(20-12)*12.5=120, y_top=220-(22.5-12)*12.5=88.75, h=31.25 -->
        <rect x="275" y="89" width="80" height="131" rx="4" fill="#C43B31" opacity="0.6"/>
        <text x="315" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="600" fill="#8B2820">20–22.5%</text>
        <text x="315" y="243" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#6B7280">Mono PERC</text>
        <text x="315" y="257" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#9CA3AF">Phasing out</text>

        <!-- TOPCon range: 22-24.5%: y_bottom=220-(22-12)*12.5=95, y_top=220-(24.5-12)*12.5=63.75, h=31.25 -->
        <rect x="405" y="64" width="80" height="156" rx="4" fill="#C43B31"/>
        <text x="445" y="59" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#C43B31">22–24.5%</text>
        <text x="445" y="243" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="600" fill="#111827">TOPCon</text>
        <text x="445" y="257" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6B7280">Market leader</text>

        <!-- HJT range: 23-25.5%: y_bottom=220-(23-12)*12.5=82.5, y_top=220-(25.5-12)*12.5=51.25, h=31.25 -->
        <rect x="535" y="51" width="80" height="169" rx="4" fill="#111827"/>
        <text x="575" y="46" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#111827">23–25.5%</text>
        <text x="575" y="243" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="600" fill="#111827">HJT</text>
        <text x="575" y="257" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6B7280">Premium</text>

        <!-- Lab record annotation -->
        <line x1="575" y1="51" x2="575" y2="28" stroke="#111827" stroke-width="1" stroke-dasharray="4"/>
        <text x="610" y="25" font-size="10" fill="#111827">Lab record: 27.09%</text>
      </svg>
    </div>
    <p class="text-xs text-neutral-muted mb-8 italic">Note: NREL certified lab record for HJT reached 27.09% (LONGi, 2024). TOPCon laboratory prototypes have achieved ~26.5%. Commercial modules remain 1.5–3% below lab records.</p>

    <!-- SECTION 3: Temperature coefficient -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-ink mb-2 mt-12">3. Temperature Performance — India's Deciding Factor</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
      This is where the technology choice gets critical for India. Panel surface temperatures in
      Rajasthan, Gujarat, and Tamil Nadu regularly hit <strong>65–80 °C</strong> in summer, while
      Standard Test Conditions (STC) are rated at just 25 °C. Every degree above 25 °C costs you
      power — and how much depends entirely on the technology.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
      The <strong>temperature coefficient of Pmax</strong> tells you the percentage power loss per
      degree Celsius above 25 °C. A module at 65 °C is 40 °C above STC. Here is what that means
      in practice:
    </p>

    <!-- Temperature coefficient chart -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl bg-neutral-snow border border-neutral-rule p-6 mb-4">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-neutral-muted mb-1">Temperature Coefficient (Pmax %/°C) — Lower is Better</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-neutral-muted mb-5">At 65°C module temp (typical India summer), each technology loses the following % of rated power:</p>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 640 220" class="w-full" role="img" aria-label="Horizontal bar chart showing temperature coefficient and power loss at 65°C for each technology">
        <!-- Background -->
        <!-- Labels on left, bars going right -->
        <!-- Scale: 0 to -0.50, with power loss at 65°C annotated -->

        <!-- Y labels and bars -->
        <!-- Poly: -0.42%/°C → at 40°C above: 16.8% loss -->
        <text x="130" y="44" text-anchor="end" font-size="12" fill="#6B7280">Polycrystalline</text>
        <rect x="140" y="28" width="235" height="28" rx="4" fill="#D1D5DB"/>
        <text x="382" y="47" font-size="11" font-weight="600" fill="#6B7280">-0.42%/°C → 16.8% loss at 65°C</text>

        <text x="130" y="99" text-anchor="end" font-size="12" fill="#C43B31" opacity="0.7">Mono PERC</text>
        <rect x="140" y="83" width="207" height="28" rx="4" fill="#C43B31" opacity="0.5"/>
        <text x="354" y="102" font-size="11" font-weight="600" fill="#8B2820">-0.37%/°C → 14.8% loss at 65°C</text>

        <text x="130" y="154" text-anchor="end" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#C43B31">TOPCon</text>
        <rect x="140" y="138" width="169" height="28" rx="4" fill="#C43B31"/>
        <text x="316" y="157" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#C43B31">-0.30%/°C → 12.0% loss at 65°C</text>

        <text x="130" y="199" text-anchor="end" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111827">HJT</text>
        <rect x="140" y="183" width="135" height="28" rx="4" fill="#111827"/>
        <text x="282" y="202" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#111827">-0.24%/°C → 9.6% loss at 65°C</text>

        <!-- Scale markers -->
        <line x1="140" y1="220" x2="375" y2="220" stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1"/>
        <text x="140" y="215" font-size="9" fill="#9CA3AF">0%</text>
        <text x="257" y="215" font-size="9" fill="#9CA3AF">-0.25%</text>
        <text x="374" y="215" font-size="9" fill="#9CA3AF">-0.50%</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <!-- Key callout -->
    <div class="rounded-xl bg-brand-red text-white p-5 mb-4">
      <p class="font-bold mb-1">The India Maths</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-white/90 leading-relaxed">
        On a 1 MW system in Rajasthan, the difference between PERC (-14.8% loss) and HJT (-9.6% loss)
        at peak summer temperatures is <strong class="text-white">52,000 extra kWh per year</strong> — roughly
        ₹3.6 lakh in avoided grid purchases at ₹7/kWh. Over 25 years: ₹90 lakh per MW installed.
        HJT's price premium often pays for itself through heat performance alone in India's hottest states.
      </p>
    </div>
    <p class="text-xs text-neutral-muted mb-8 italic">Sources: SunPal Solar (2024); Mongabay India (2024); Scientific Reports — experimental analysis of PV module performance in elevated temperatures.</p>

    <!-- SECTION 4: Market Share -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-ink mb-2 mt-12">4. The Market Shift: N-Type Takes Over</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
      The industry's pivot to n-type (TOPCon + HJT) has been the fastest technology transition in
      solar history. In 2022, PERC held 60% of the market. By end of 2024, n-type accounted for
      over 75% of global production. Understanding this shift matters for long-term warranty and
      supply support.
    </p>

    <!-- Market share chart -->
    <div class="rounded-2xl bg-neutral-snow border border-neutral-rule p-6 mb-3">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-neutral-muted mb-5">Global PV Module Market Share 2022 → 2024</p>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 640 300" class="w-full" role="img" aria-label="Grouped bar chart showing market share shifts of solar technologies from 2022 to 2024">
        <!-- Grid -->
        <line x1="60" y1="20" x2="600" y2="20" stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1"/>
        <line x1="60" y1="68" x2="600" y2="68" stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1"/>
        <line x1="60" y1="116" x2="600" y2="116" stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1"/>
        <line x1="60" y1="164" x2="600" y2="164" stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1"/>
        <line x1="60" y1="212" x2="600" y2="212" stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1"/>
        <line x1="60" y1="240" x2="600" y2="240" stroke="#E5E7EB" stroke-width="1"/>

        <!-- Y axis labels -->
        <text x="52" y="24" text-anchor="end" font-size="11" fill="#6B7280">80%</text>
        <text x="52" y="72" text-anchor="end" font-size="11" fill="#6B7280">60%</text>
        <text x="52" y="120" text-anchor="end" font-size="11" fill="#6B7280">40%</text>
        <text x="52" y="168" text-anchor="end" font-size="11" fill="#6B7280">20%</text>
        <text x="52" y="212" text-anchor="end" font-size="11" fill="#6B7280">0%</text>

        <!-- Scale: 0%=212, 80%=20, so 1%=2.4px -->
        <!-- 2022 group: x starts 80 -->
        <text x="145" y="265" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#374151">2022</text>
        <!-- Poly 3%: h=7.2, y=204.8 -->
        <rect x="80" y="205" width="28" height="7" rx="2" fill="#9CA3AF"/>
        <text x="94" y="200" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9CA3AF">3%</text>
        <!-- PERC 60%: h=144, y=68 -->
        <rect x="112" y="68" width="28" height="144" rx="2" fill="#C43B31" opacity="0.55"/>
        <text x="126" y="63" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="600" fill="#8B2820">60%</text>
        <!-- TOPCon 10%: h=24, y=188 -->
        <rect x="144" y="188" width="28" height="24" rx="2" fill="#C43B31"/>
        <text x="158" y="183" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#C43B31">10%</text>
        <!-- HJT 3%: h=7, y=205 -->
        <rect x="176" y="205" width="28" height="7" rx="2" fill="#111827"/>
        <text x="190" y="200" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#111827">3%</text>

        <!-- 2023 group -->
        <text x="335" y="265" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#374151">2023</text>
        <!-- Poly ~1%: h=2.4 -->
        <rect x="265" y="209" width="28" height="3" rx="2" fill="#9CA3AF"/>
        <text x="279" y="205" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9CA3AF">~1%</text>
        <!-- PERC 63%: h=151 -->
        <rect x="297" y="61" width="28" height="151" rx="2" fill="#C43B31" opacity="0.55"/>
        <text x="311" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="600" fill="#8B2820">63%</text>
        <!-- TOPCon 25%: h=60 -->
        <rect x="329" y="152" width="28" height="60" rx="2" fill="#C43B31"/>
        <text x="343" y="147" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#C43B31">25%</text>
        <!-- HJT 9%: h=22 -->
        <rect x="361" y="190" width="28" height="22" rx="2" fill="#111827"/>
        <text x="375" y="185" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#111827">9%</text>

        <!-- 2024 group -->
        <text x="520" y="265" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="600" fill="#374151">2024</text>
        <!-- Poly 0%: none -->
        <rect x="449" y="211" width="28" height="1" rx="2" fill="#9CA3AF"/>
        <text x="463" y="207" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#9CA3AF">0%</text>
        <!-- PERC 43%: h=103 -->
        <rect x="481" y="109" width="28" height="103" rx="2" fill="#C43B31" opacity="0.45"/>
        <text x="495" y="104" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" font-weight="600" fill="#8B2820">43%</text>
