      </svg>
    </div>
    <p class="text-xs text-neutral-muted mb-8 italic">Sources: EnergyBin Global PV Module Market Analysis 2025; InfoLink 2024 global shipment ranking; NREL Spring 2025 Solar Industry Update.</p>

    <!-- SECTION 5: Degradation -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-ink mb-2 mt-12">5. Degradation Rates — The Long Game</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed mb-4">
      Degradation is the slow death of your investment. A 0.5%/year vs 0.27%/year difference
      sounds small — but compounded over 25 years, it means the difference between a system
      that performs at 88% of original capacity versus one still performing at 94%.
    </p>
    <p class="text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
      N-type technologies (TOPCon, HJT) have a structural advantage: they eliminate
      <strong>Light-Induced Degradation (LID)</strong>, a first-year drop of up to 2% in p-type
      PERC panels caused by boron-oxygen defects activating under sunlight. PERC panels lose
      this in year 1 before they even start their 25-year count.
    </p>

