    <!-- SECTION 6: Bifaciality -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-ink mb-2 mt-12">6. Bifaciality — Free Energy from the Rear</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Bifacial modules generate power from both faces. The rear collects light reflected off the
      ground, roof, or surrounding surfaces. The ratio of rear-to-front generation potential is the
      <strong>bifaciality factor</strong>. In India, white concrete rooftops can achieve 15–25% rear
      gain, and ground-mount installations with white gravel reflectors have measured up to 30% gain.
      HJT's symmetric amorphous silicon structure gives it the industry's best bifaciality.
    </p>

    <div class="rounded-2xl bg-neutral-snow border border-neutral-rule p-6 mb-8">
